\msec {Simplified Money Formatting}

Often, one merely wishes to format a numeric vector. So the rrv package, also provide the functions moneyp and moneyf, for printing (formatted) and formatting respectively, numeric vectors as money. These functions also use the same arguments as the constructor.
<<>>=
#create some new random numbers
v = 5e5 * rnorm (20)
@

<<>>=
#format as money 
moneyf (v, fill=FALSE)
@




